## 2. API Contracts & Payloads
To ensure successful communication between modules, n8n (Tanner) and Unity (Megan) will use the following standard JSON structures for phase 1 testing.

**Standard Outbound Payload (Unity to n8n):**
json
{
  "session_id": "aot_test_001",
  "user_message": "Hello A.O.T, what is the status of the system?",
  "timestamp": "2026-03-10T12:00:00Z"
}

**Standard Inbound Payload (n8n to Unity):
json
{
  "status": "success",
  "ai_response": "All systems are currently functioning at optimal capacity.",
  "emotion_state": "Neutral"
}

